transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hey, Ron?

Speaker 2: Yes.

Speaker 1: Hey, bud.

Speaker 2: Thanks for holding.

Speaker 1: Thanks for being patient.

Speaker 2: So, I did three things for you, bud.

Speaker 1: The first thing I did is I put a stop to any and all monthly shipments.

Speaker 2: The second thing I did is I put a stop to any and all monthly refills.

Speaker 1: The third thing I did is I put a stop to any and all monthly charges, and I reversed the—

Speaker 2: charge of the $63.95 that was trying to be charged, and then you'll get that immediately,

Speaker 1: and I put a stop to the refill, right?

Speaker 2: I was able to catch that, so kudos to you for, like, calling in, because what I found—

Speaker 1: is what really grinds my gears, bud, and really pisses me off and flips my lid is I noticed—

Speaker 2: that you didn't even get the AGD, so I replaced it.

Speaker 1: You got the basic Viagra, so I replaced it for free.

Speaker 2: It doesn't cost you anything, right?

Speaker 1: I'm billing the damn doctor because the pharmacy or the doctor, I don't know, sent you the—

Speaker 2: wrong stuff, so when you get these, Ron, they're going to be white diamond, but they'll—

Speaker 1: say 50 on them, okay?

Speaker 2: Okay, yeah, that's why I did it, because it was the, yeah, they weren't the correct ones,

Speaker 1: so that's why I can't go slow.

Speaker 2: Yeah, so, okay, so don't worry, so I put a stop to everything.

Speaker 1: I sent you a replacement.

Speaker 2: I credit back your account of the $63.95, and in light of this, give me the thumbs up—

Speaker 1: after you receive these and you try them, and let me know how you want to do things,

Speaker 2: and then we'll go from there, and I can always set it up where you get refills when you want—

Speaker 1: by clicking a button or calling me, all right?

Speaker 2: We'll do it that way, but let's get you the stuff that you really wanted, and we'll go—

Speaker 1: from there, all right, Ron?

Speaker 2: Be on the lookout for them.

Speaker 1: There'll be white pills, and they'll get there by Saturday or Monday, all right, bud?

Speaker 2: Perfect.

Speaker 1: I appreciate it.

Speaker 2: Yeah, of course, bud.

Speaker 1: Take care, and go Hawks.

Speaker 2: Thanks a lot.

Speaker 1: All right.

Speaker 2: Adios.
